    "body": "### Problem\n\nFrom here: https://github.com/j-hui/fidget.nvim/issues/117\r\n\r\nWhen `winblend=100` is set for a floating window, the borders don't seem to inherit the background highlight from the window beneath it.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nEvaluate this file:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n-- winblendnt.lua\r\nlocal b = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\nlocal w = vim.api.nvim_open_win(b, false, {\r\n  relative = \"editor\",\r\n  width = 5,\r\n  height = 2,\r\n  row = 5,\r\n  col = 30,\r\n  style = \"minimal\",\r\n  border = \"single\",\r\n})\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_win_call(w, function()\r\n  vim.cmd \"setlocal winblend=100\"\r\nend)\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(b, 0, -1, false, {\"\", \" b \"})\r\n\r\nvim.opt.termguicolors = true\r\nvim.cmd \"hi CursorLine guibg=#2a2b3d\"\r\n\r\nvim.opt.cursorline = true\r\n\r\nvim.cmd \"8\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nRun with something like:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nnvim -u NONE winblendnt.lua '+luafile %'\r\n```\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/11800204/29a0f5ad-2dcc-4c9d-b178-9e5209a6d27b)\r\n\r\nAs shown in the screenshot, the window contents (including text) correctly inherits the underlying background from the cursorline, but the border characters do not.\r\n\r\nIt looks even worse when the cursorline is aligned with one of the horizontal borders:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/11800204/d0df4f0e-459f-406b-bf36-4614c2e33644)\r\n\r\nI get a similar issue when I highlight a line using visual mode, so it's not unique to `cursorline`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`winblend` should also apply to border characters.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1521+ge9b9a86cd\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 13.4\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.30.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
